\"addressCountry\":\"US\"},\"image\":\"/images/parks/northcarolina/apex-nature-park/apex-nature-park-1.jpg\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I walk my dog indoors in Apex, NC?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes. Our directory currently lists 20 indoor dog parks in Apex. Use the “Indoor Dog Park” filter on this page to jump straight to climate-controlled options.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Does Apex have a public dog park?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, the Apex Nature Park and Hunter Street Dog Park are popular off-leash areas. Both require a pass for entry, ensuring a safe environment for vaccinated dogs.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are there dog-friendly trails in Apex?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Absolutely. The Beaver Creek Greenway offers paved, scenic routes perfect for leashed walks. Salem Pond Park also provides a pleasant loop for a quick outing.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the leash laws in Apex?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Apex maintains strict leash laws. Dogs must be on a leash and under the control of their owner when outside of their own property or designated off-leash areas.\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Dog Parks Directory\",\"item\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Apex\"}]}</script><header class=\"header header-visible  header-light\"><div class=\"header-container\"><div class=\"header-left\"><a class=\"logo\" href=\"/\"><img alt=\"Indoor Dog Park logo\" width=\